.TH JOB-ASSETS-CLAUDE 1 "March 2026" "job-assets-claude" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
job-assets-claude \- run the job-assets CLI with Claude as the default provider
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B job-assets-claude
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B job-assets-claude
\fIJD_SOURCE\fR [\fICOMPANY\fR] [\fIROLE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B job-assets-claude
behaves like
.BR job-assets ,
but defaults the provider to
.BR claude .
Its Claude-backed runs explicitly request
.B claude-sonnet-4-6
with
.B --effort max
unless
.BR CLAUDE_MODEL ,
.BR CLAUDE_EFFORT ,
 .BR CLAUDE_PERMISSION_MODE ,
or
.BR CLAUDE_EXTRA_ARGS
override them.
The non-interactive argv keeps
.B --print
immediately before the prompt so newer Claude CLI builds do not drop it.
Submit-time Claude runs use the same centralized submit-mode tool allowlist as the rest of the repo, so board-specific answer generation stays aligned with the main asset pipeline.
If the first argument is a job description URL or file path, it runs the single-job
.B pipeline
flow and stops at review unless
.B --submit
is also present.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B job-assets-claude https://boards.greenhouse.io/company/jobs/12345
Run the end-to-end single-job flow with Claude.
.TP
.B job-assets-claude --submit https://boards.greenhouse.io/company/jobs/12345
Run the end-to-end single-job flow with Claude and submit after review.
.TP
.B job-assets-claude batch --dry-run
Run the standard high-throughput batch workflow with Claude.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR job-assets (1),
.BR job-assets-codex (1)
